The paper focuses on developing a hashing method based on 2D image features for retrieval, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of supervised learning and optimization strategies, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on benchmark datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper utilizes features from both traditional and deep learning methods, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
